<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="363" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                    <head>No. 299.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Stevens</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-05-02"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 2,
                            1882</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 125.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your dispatch No. 125, of the
                        17th ultimo, relating to two cases in which the naturalization was disputed,
                        by the Swedish <pb facs="0563" n="491" xml:id="pg_491"/> authorities, of one
                        C. M. Cedergren and one Peder Sigbjornsen, Skoland.</p>
                    <p>Your action, as reported in the said dispatch, is approved.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                </div>
            </body></text></TEI>